channeldata.description: Python Client for Google Cloud Bigtable -------------------------  [Google Cloud Bigtable](https://cloud.google.com/bigtable) is Google's NoSQL Big Data database service. It's the same database that powers many core Google services, including Search, Analytics, Maps, and Gmail.  - [Client Library Documentation](https://googleapis.github.io/google-cloud-python/latest/bigtable/usage.html) - [Product Documentation](https://cloud.google.com/bigtable/docs)  Quick Start -----------  In order to use this library, you first need to go through the following steps:  1. [Select or create a Cloud Platform project.](https://console.cloud.google.com/project) 2. [Enable billing for your project.](https://cloud.google.com/billing/docs/how-to/modify-project#enable_billing_for_a_project) 3. [Enable the Cloud Bigtable API.](https://cloud.google.com/bigtable) 4. [Setup Authentication.](https://googleapis.github.io/google-cloud-python/latest/core/auth.html)  Supported Python Versions ------------------------- Python >= 3.5  Deprecated Python Versions ------------------------- Python == 2.7. Python 2.7 support will be removed on January 1, 2020.
channeldata.summary: Python Client for Google Cloud Bigtable
